Description: Step forward and straighten your leg, lifting your toes off the ground as you lean down, moving your arms in a scooping motion. Straighten back up and repeat on the other leg as you take another step forward.

Display Name: Knee Hug to Lunge with Reach
Exercise: Knee Hug to Lunge with Reach
Description: In a standing position, bring your knee to your chest and wrap your hands around your shin to pull your knee farther up. Release that leg and step it forward, dropping into a lunge. Reach the opposite arm up and over the head to stretch the hip. Push up to standing with the back leg, then repeat on the other side.

Take a step then lean forward, bring the back leg off the ground. Extend your arms out in front of you, making a straight line from your hands down to the foot off the ground. Stand back up and take a step forward with the leg that was raised, and repeat.
Standing in place, bring your knee out and move it in toward your midline to "close" your hips. Complete for the set number of reps.
Standing in place, bring your knee up and move it out away from your midline to "open" your hips. Complete for the set number of reps.

Laying on your back with your arms in a T-position, bring one leg up toward the opposite arm as far as you can without lifting your midback off the ground. Bring that leg back down to the starting position, then repeat on the other side. Complete for the set number of reps.
Skip with minimal movement, keeping your steps small and jump height relatively low.
Skip to reach maximal height, driving one knee and your opposite arm into the air at the same time.
In a standing position, flex your knee to kick your heel up to your glute. Repeat this motion, alternating each leg and moving at a quick pace.

Stand feet shoulder-width apart, knees and hips bent in a half-squat position. Shuffle your feet to one side, taking 4 steps before coming to a stop. Shuffle back in the opposite direction. Be sure to stay squatted throughout the entire movement.

Standing feet shoulder-width apart, cross one leg over the other. Next, step your back foot out so you are in the starting position. Cross the first foot behind your other foot. Step the front foot out to be back in the starting position. Repeat this motion quickly, then perform the exercise again in the other direction.
Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Jog backward the designated distance, then turn around and jog backward to the starting point.
Jog in place, driving your knees high into the air with every step.

Start feet shoulder-width a part. Bend your knees, swinging your arms behind you, then jump to your right and land only on your right leg. Immediately, jump back to the starting position but land only on your left leg. Repeat for the set number of reps.
Stand feet shoulder-width apart and bend your knees graciously, swinging your arms up as you jump up. As soon as you land, bend your knees and jump again. Complete for the set number of reps.
You will be jumping for distance. Be sure to use your arms to increase your power during your jump. Complete for the set number of reps.
Jump forward 3 times on one leg, trying to maximize your distance for each jump. Repeat on the opposite leg.

Set up markers 5 yards wide in a zig-zag shape the length of the designated distance. Begin in an athletic position. Quickly run 5 yards to the left while facing forward, then switch directions and run to the right. Continue for the designated distance.

Set up 4 markers in a square shape. Begin at the bottom right marker. Run straight ahead to the top right marker, shuffle left to the top left marker, backpedal to the bottom left marker, then shuffle right to the starting marker. Repeat for the set number of reps.
Start on one end of the field and sprint 30 yards.
Start on one end of the field and bound forward 30 yards, extending the legs fully and swinging the arms with every step.

Set up 4 markers in a square shape. Begin at the bottom right marker and run straight ahead to the top of the box. Plant and cut to the left, heading toward the top left marker. Complete the box for one rep, planting and cutting to the left at each marker. Repeat in the opposite direction.
Use a wall for support if needed. Keep your torso straight as you swing your leg backward as far as you can, then swing it forward. Complete for the set number of reps.
Skip forward and swing your arms around in circles forward, then backward.
Begin in a half-squat position with your hands on your hips. Shift your weight to one side, then shift your weight to the other. Complete for the set number of reps.
Step forward into a lunge, then rotate your torso to face the left, then rotate to face the right. Push up off your back leg to stand again. Step forward into a lunge with the other leg, and repeat.

Step backward into a lunge, then reach up with the arm on the same side of your back leg. Reach up and over your body to feel a stretch through your side. Push up with your front leg into a standing position, then repeat on the opposite side.

Begin in an athletic position with one foot in front of the other. Pivot your hips to switch your stance quickly, so the back foot is now in front. Repeat these stance switches quickly for the designated time.

Begin in an athletic position. Squat low and push off the ground with one foot, diving laterally in the opposite direction. Stand back up and repeat in the other direction. Be sure to complete this drill on grass to soften the landings from the dives.
Hop up and down on both feet, making sure the motion is coming from the ankle. Your knees should not be bending when you land on the ground. Repeat for the designated time.

Begin in a crouched position, then jump up and extend all of your limbs at the same time. When you land, immediately drop back into the crouched position, then repeat the jumps for the set number of reps.
Begin with feet shoulder-width apart. Jump laterally about 4 feet, landing with both feet on the ground. Immediately jump back to the starting position. Repeat for the set number of reps.
Begin standing on one leg. Jump forward and land on the same leg, maintaining your balance. Continue hopping forward for the set distance, then turn and jump the same distance on the opposite leg.

Set up 4 markers in a square shape. Begin at the bottom right marker. Run diagonally to the the top left marker, shuffle to the top right marker, backpedal to the bottom left marker, then shuffle right to the starting marker. Repeat for the set number of reps.

Set up 4 markers in a square shape. Begin at the bottom right marker. Run straight ahead to the the top right marker, backpedal to the bottom left marker, then run straight ahead to the top left marker. Repeat for the set number of reps.

Begin on your hands and knees. Lift your knees off the ground and crawl forward on your hands and toes. Crawl the designated distance, then crawl backward, leading with your feet. Repeat for the set number of reps.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hug one knee as close as you can into your chest. Hold for 1-2 seconds, then release and repeat on the other side.

Lift one leg and grab your foot, bringing it toward your rear to stretch your quad. Reach the opposite arm all the way up, then stand up on your toes. Hold for 1-2 seconds, then release and repeat on the other side.
Take a step forward, then kick the opposite leg toward your opposte outstretched arm. Release back down, then repeat on the other leg as you walk forward.

Begin on your stomach with your arms in a T-shape. Bring your heel up toward your opposite arm, twisting your torso up but keeping your chest on the ground. Release to the ground and repeat on the other side.
Stand with your hands on your hips. Circle your hips clockwise, then counterclockwise.

Holding a resistance band, step out into a lateral lunge. As your descend into the lunge, bring your arms up over your head and pull against the resistance band. Release and go back to standing, then repeat on the other side.

Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Hold the resistance band and raise your arms over your head. Pull against the resistance as you bend to one side. Hold for 1-2 seconds, then release and repeat on the other side.
Stand feet slightly wider than shoulder-width. Squat with proper form then stand back up and go onto your toes. Repeat for the designated reps.
Begin in a lunged position. Jump up, then switch legs before you hit the ground. Continue to jump and switch legs with every rep.

Place a small resistance band around your ankles. Step out until you feel adequate resistance in the band. Stand up onto your toes to perform a calf raise against the resistance of the band. Repeat for the designated reps.

Place one end of a large resistance band around your foot, anchoring it to the ground. Grasp the other end of the band in your hands and pull up on the band, twisting your torso away from the foot holding the band down. Release and complete for the designated reps, then repeat on the other side.

Place a small resistance band around your ankles. Get into a plank position on your elbows, then step one foot out and back to center. Repeat on the other side. Complete for the designated reps, maintain the plank position throughout the exercise.
Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Step back into a lunge, then stand back up and drive the knee of the back leg up. Complete all of the designated reps on one side, then switch sides and repeat.

On one leg, hop diagonally to the right, then back to the starting position, then diagonally to the left, then back to the starting position. Complete for the designated amount of time, then repeat on the other side.
Balancing on one leg, keep your core tight as you reach down with the opposite arm and touch your toes. Extend your other leg out behind you as you reach down. Complete for the designated reps.

Set up 5 markers in a "plus" shape. Begin at the middle marker. Run to the top marker, shuffle diagonally to the leftmost marker, then run all the way across to the right most marker. Shuffle back diagonally to the bottom marker, then run back to start. Repeat for the designated reps.

Set up 5 markers in a small X shape. Begin at the top right marker. On one foot, hop from the top right to the top left, then to the middle, then to the bottom right, then finish at the bottom left. Hop back to start in backward order. Repeat on the other foot. Complete for the designated reps.

Stand feet slightly wider than shoulder-width. Perform a deep squat, swinging your arms back and then explode upward as high as you can. When you land, go straight back into a squat. Perform three of these jumps in a row before resting; this is one set. Complete the designated number of sets.

Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Perform a squat but shift your weight onto one side so your body is off-center. Come back to the starting position, then perform the squat on the other side. Repeat for the designated reps.
Stand feet slightly wider than shoulder-width. Squat with proper form then jump straight up, landing in the squat position. Continue for the designated reps.

Stand on one leg. Your other leg should be bent at the hip and knee. Lean forward and touch your toes, extending your raised leg behind you. Stand back up and drive your knee up, maintaining your balance. Repeat for the designated reps.

Sit with your feet elevated off the floor, knees bent toward your torso. Twist the top half of your body toward one side and twist your knees in the other direction. Without putting your feet on the floor, switch sides. This is one rep. Continue for the designated reps.

Sit with your feet outstretched and your torso leaned back slightly. Bring your knees in toward your chest, meeting your knees in the middle. Extend back all the way, keeping your feet elevated. Complete for the designated reps.

Lay down on your back. Keep your hands by your sides, engage your core, and lift your legs up as far as you can. Make sure your back stays flush with the ground as your lower back to the ground. Do not let your feet touch the floor between reps. Complete for the designated reps.

Place your hands on a box, feet on the ground as you hold your self up. Bend your elbows and allow your body to descend. Only use your arms to lift your body back up. Complete for the designated reps.
Begin in a plank position on your hands. Bring one knee in toward your chest. Switch legs quickly to complete one rep. Keep your back straight throughout the duration of the exercise.
Get into a pushup position with your hands on an elevated surface, ideally a box or bench. Perform a pushup regularly, keeping your back straight and your core tight.
Begin in a plank position on your hands. Alternate tapping your shoulders with the opposite arms. Be sure to keep your body in line and core tight as you move. Complete for the designated time.
Skip forward, driving your knee upward and keeping the other leg fully extended. Alternate legs, making sure to let both touch the ground in between skips.
Skip forward, kicking one leg out and keeping the other leg fully extended. Alternate legs, making sure to let both touch the ground in between skips.
Use your arms and legs to power your jump. Squat down, then explode upward. While in the air, try to bring your knees as close to your chest as possible before you land.
Stand feet wider than shoulder-width. Perform a deep squat, then push off the ground and jump upward as high as you can. When you land, go straight back into the deep squat.
Stand in front of a box. Bend your knees then jump onto the box, swinging your arms to generate more momentum. Be sure to land on the box with both feet at the same time, stabilizing your landing.

On one leg, bend forward with a straight back, reaching toward the floor. Jump upward, straightening through your spine and swinging your back leg forward. Be sure to maintain your stability when you land.
On one leg, hop forward, left, backward, and then right. Continue to hop in this square shape for the designated reps, then switch legs and repeat.

Stand on your right leg. Jump as far as you can to the right, landing on your right leg. Immediately jump forward as far as you can, landing on your left leg. Finally, jump forward as far as you can again, this time landing on both legs. Repeat the same process with your left leg, jumping left first.

Perform a side plank on your elbow. Extend through your top leg and lift it up, holding the position for 1-2 seconds. Be sure to maintain a tight core. Release back down, then repeat for the designated reps.
Start on your stomach, hands braced by your shoulders. Lift up into a plank position, then perform a pushup. Immediately hop your legs toward your hands, then sprint 10 yards.

Start with a slow jog, taking small steps. After a few steps, hike one leg up with a high knee drive and strike your foot back down quickly. Take a few more steps, then repeat on the other leg. Complete for the designated distance.
